Setup Instructions for Ubuntu 12
================================

1. Install needed packages
sudo apt-get install curl git zsh

(Log out/in to setup zsh defaults?)

15.  Install oh-my-zsh
https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh#via-wget
curl -L http://install.ohmyz.sh | sh

** potentiall having issues with this step due to lack of sudo / PAM access
** switch to "manual" instll steps

20. Install Oracle's Java 7
http://www.webupd8.org/2012/01/install-oracle-java-jdk-7-in-ubuntu-via.html

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/java
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install oracle-java7-installer
sudo apt-get install oracle-java7-set-default

verify
 sudo update-alternatives --config javac

30. Install Ruby (via rvm)
http://rvm.io/rvm/install
user$ \curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable

** this isn't working as well as expected, is zsh to blame?
found an answer http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9336596/rvm-installation-not-working-rvm-is-not-a-function


40. Install ant
sudo apt-get install ant

45. Install maven
sudo apt-get install maven

50. Install Groovy/Gradle (via gvm)
http://gvmtool.net/
curl -s get.gvmtool.net | bash

gvm install groovy
gvm install gradle


Other
installed Chromium from "Ubuntu Software Center"
